The '''Dark Jedi Conflict''' took place from [[188 BBY]] to [[181 BBY/Legends|181 BBY]] in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]]. In 188 BBY, [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Kibh Jeen]] was affected by the [[Almas Sith fortress|Sith fortress]] on the planet [[Almas]] and fell to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. The fortress' influence caused Jeen to betray and murder his [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]], [[Qornah]]. Jeen forced the [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] of the [[Cularin asteroid belt|system's asteroid belt]] to become his slaves, setting the stage for the battle. He began with a [[Battle of Genarius (Dark Jedi Conflict)|ruthless attack]] on the floating cities of [[Genarius]].<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Kibh Jeen became one of the first to discover that the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] had survived the [[Seventh Battle of Ruusan]], and now hid themselves away from [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] notice by observing [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane's]] [[Rule of Two/Legends|Rule of Two]]. Although Jeen's "mad rantings" were dismissed by the Jedi, they would later regret their "lack of faith."<ref name="END">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

Seen as too dangerous to be left alive, the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] sent a [[Unidentified Jedi Knight (Dark Jedi Conflict)|Jedi Knight]] and [[Unidentified Padawan (Dark Jedi Conflict)|her Padawan]] to hunt down and kill their former compatriot. They gathered an armada formed of ships from the system's various settlements and companies, which they used to [[Final battle of the Dark Jedi Conflict|crush]] the pirate fleet. In 181 BBY, they succeeded in resolving the danger, but were forced to slay Jeen in the process.<ref name="LFC" />

The [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] decided to build a [[Almas Academy|Jedi academy]] on the other side of the planet, to monitor the Sith fortress and prevent similar events.<ref name="LFC" />

